    <statement><div><p>
A square plot of land in <alert>Konzaa city</alert> has an area of <m>\sqrt{{2}}</m> hectares. By applying logarithms, write <m>\sqrt{{2}}</m> in terms of <m>\log {2}</m>.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  
</p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
First, rewrite the square root as a fractional index:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\sqrt{{2}} = {2}^{1/2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Now apply the logarithm law:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log(a^n) = n\log a
</me>
</p>

<p>
So,
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log(\sqrt{{2}}) = \log({2}^{1/2}) = \frac{1}{2}\log {2}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the correct answer is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{\frac{1}{2}\log {2}}
</me>
</p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\frac{\ln \left( 2 \right)}{2}</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>